description.narrative: (Kenya): .This activity supports the journey to self-reliance in Kilifi County by building commitment and capacity to strengthen health systems and ensure achievement of health goals in family planning, maternal, newborn, child, and adolescent health (RMNCAH), nutrition, and water, sanitation, and hygiene (WASH) services. It will build the leadership and management capacity of Kilifi County to finance and implement its health programs through prioritizing domestic resource mobilization, especially for the financing of RMNCAH services. This activity will enhance the capacity of county and sub-county teams to plan, coordinate, implement, monitor, and evaluate RMNCAH, nutrition, and WASH services. This approach will be anchored in co-creation and co-investment with the county and other stakeholders to enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of the health information systems, integrated supply chain systems, and human resources for health systems. Health workers contracted by USAID under the previous mechanism will be transitioned to the county payroll. To increase accountability for quality health services, this mechanism will use a co-creation approach to establish sub-county mentorship teams that conduct supportive supervision activities and build technical skills of health and community health workers. Sub-county teams will develop community-demand creation activities to increase utilization of health services and expand adolescent responsive services to address high teenage pregnancy rates within Kilifi County. By utilizing a health systems strengthening approach, the project ensures sustainability upon project completion, which is vital to achieving the Kenya Integrated Country Strategy Goal three, and U.S. Department of State and USAID Joint Strategic Plan 2018-2022 objective, which seeks to promote healthy, educated, and productive populations to drive inclusive and sustainable development..
